      "text": "**Anterior cingulate cortex**\nThe anterior cingulate cortex (ACC) plays a significant role in motivation and the creation of emotion. An emotion can be seen as comprising both a feeling and a motivation based on that feeling. According to one view, the \"feeling\" is represented in the insula, while the \"motivation\" is represented in the ACC. _Many interoceptive tasks activate the insula and ACC together_, specifically tasks that elicit strong aversive feeling states like pain. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interoception#Anterior_insular_cortex wikipedia]"
